HEADWORD: Pinole
<hw>Pi*nole"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
aromatic powder used in Italy in the manufacture of chocolate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Parched maize, ground, and mixed with sugar, etc.
Mixed with water, it makes a nutritious beverage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pi⟦ntil⟧on</ent>⟦br⟧
